#: ../../developer/releases/4_2/release-notes.rst:70
#: 4ce00116912a4ad8a1f803514434b894
msgid ""
"DomU firewalls have completely switched to nftables. Users should add "
"their custom rules to the ``custom-input`` and ``custom-forward`` chains."
" (For more information, see issues `#5031 <https://github.com/QubesOS"
"/qubes-issues/issues/5031>`__ and `#6062 <https://github.com/QubesOS"
"/qubes-issues/issues/6062>`__.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/releases/4_2/release-notes.rst:72
#: ce3cc0cade2b4ef08318e8c787748470
msgid ""
"Templates restored in 4.2 from a pre-4.2 backup continue to target their "
"original Qubes OS release repos. If you are using fresh templates on a "
"clean 4.2 installation, or if you performed an :ref:`in-place upgrade "
"from 4.1 to 4.2 <user/downloading-installing-upgrading/upgrade/4_2:in-"
"place upgrade>`, then this does not affect you. (For more information, "
"see issue `#8701 <https://github.com/QubesOS/qubes-"
"issues/issues/8701>`__.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/releases/4_2/release-notes.rst:76
